        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:19:2",
        "text": [
          " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) إِذَا زَنَى الرَّجُلُ فَجُلِدَ يَنْبَغِي لِلْإِمَامِ أَنْ يَنْفِيَهُ مِنَ الْأَرْضِ الَّتِي جُلِدَ فِيهَا إِلَى غَيْرِهَا فَإِنَّمَا عَلَى الْإِمَامِ أَنْ يُخْرِجَهُ مِنَ الْمِصْرِ الَّذِي جُلِدَ فِيهِ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from Muhammad Bin Isa, from Yunus, from Zurara, from Sama’at who said, ",
            "‘Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘When the man commits adultery, so he is whipped, it is befitting for the Imam<sup>asws</sup> that he<sup>asws</sup> exiles him from the land wherein he was whipped to other than it. But rather, it is upon the Imam<sup>asws</sup> than he exits him from the city in which he was whipped’."
          ]
        }
      },
